@scoobyboy

If you can't copy files larger than 4 GB you might have FAT32 as the file system on that HD. Try to convert to NTFS (in Windows use command "convert drive_letter: /fs:ntfs") or if you're using Linux then use ext4.

It's actually 46.61 GB and that's closer to 50 GB (compared to the 5.0 GB you mentioned) and that requires a Blu-Ray Dual Layer disc (BD-R DL or BD-RE DL) if you want to make an optical disc to play in a BD 3D compatible player.
